"    <div id=\"topicTitle\">",
"     Patient information: Transient tachypnea of the newborn (The Basics)",
"    </div>",
"    <span class=\"view\">",
"     View in",
"     <a class=\"lang\" href=\"./es-419/transient-tachypnea-of-the-newborn-the-basics?source=topic_page\">",
"      Spanish",
"     </a>",
"    </span>",
"    <a class=\"contributor contributor_credentials\" href=\"./authors-and-editors/patient-information\">",
"     Written by the doctors and editors at UpToDate",
"    </a>",
"    <div id=\"topicText\">",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H23424356\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What is transient tachypnea of the newborn?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Transient tachypnea of the newborn (called &ldquo;TTN&rdquo; here) is a condition that causes breathing problems in newborn babies.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Babies have fluid in their lungs before birth. The fluid normally goes away when a baby is born. In some babies, the fluid does not go away as quickly as it should. This causes TTN.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      A mother who has diabetes, asthma, or a c-section without labor is more likely to have a baby with TTN. A c-section is also called a &ldquo;cesarean delivery.&rdquo; It is a type of surgery used to deliver a baby.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H23424371\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What are the symptoms of TTN?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Symptoms usually happen within 2 hours after birth. They include:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Fast breathing &ndash; More than 60 breaths a minute. This is more than 1 breath every second.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Skin that looks blue",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Hard breathing &ndash; This can include:",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"hyphen-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Nostrils that open wide when the baby takes a breath",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Skin and muscles that look like they are caving in - This can happen between the baby&rsquo;s ribs or under the baby&rsquo;s ribcage.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Grunting when the baby breathes out",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Symptoms of TTN usually last 12 to 72 hours.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H23424386\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Is there a test for TTN?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;No, there is no single test. The doctor or nurse can often tell if a baby has TTN by doing an exam.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Other conditions can cause breathing problems similar to TTN. These include serious conditions such as pneumonia. The doctor can order a chest X-ray that shows changes in the lungs. Looking at the X-ray can help the doctor learn if a baby has TTN or a different condition.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H23424400\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       How is TTN treated?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;TTN usually goes away by the time a baby is 3 days old. Until that happens, doctors can help the baby get enough oxygen and nutrition if he or she needs it. Treatments might include:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Extra oxygen &ndash; This helps make sure the baby has enough oxygen in his or her blood.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Temperature control &ndash; This keeps the baby from getting too hot or too cold.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        A feeding tube or &ldquo;IV&rdquo; &ndash; If the baby has trouble breathing, he or she might not be able to nurse or drink from a bottle. A feeding tube is a small tube that goes into the baby&rsquo;s mouth or nose, down the throat, and into the stomach. It can be used to put breast milk or formula right into the baby&rsquo;s stomach.",
"        <br/>",
"        <br/>",
"        An IV is a thin tube that goes into a vein. It can carry a sugar mixture into the baby&rsquo;s bloodstream.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Antibiotics &ndash; These are medicines to keep infections from happening or stop them if they do happen.",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H23424415\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       More on this topic",
"      </span>",
"     </p>",
